text: Geiswiller-Zœbersdorf is a commune. It is in Grand Est in the Bas-Rhin department in northeast France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2018 and consists of the former communes of Geiswiller (the seat) and Zœbersdorf.Arrêté préfectoral 28 December 2017 == References == Category:2018 establishments in France Category:Communes in Bas-Rhin
